<p>Here we could define and handle the json request or response of the connector while the API rest services are invoked.
 <img src="/images/2016-09-16-Lisbon-summer-camp-mobile-learning-2016/MCS-APISimplementationJson.jpg" alt="" /></p>

<p>Finally, repackage the archive, upload it to MCS, test in MCS UI and publish.</p>

<p><img src="/images/2016-09-16-Lisbon-summer-camp-mobile-learning-2016/MCS-APISimplementationTesting.jpg" alt="" /></p>

<h3 id="create-a-mobile-application-with-oracle-max">Create a mobile application with Oracle MAX</h3>

<p>Go back to MCS Applications and select mobile Applications.</p>

<p><img src="/images/2016-09-16-Lisbon-summer-camp-mobile-learning-2016/MCS-MobileApplication.jpg" alt="" /></p>

<p>We created a new application in the Mobile Application Accelerator (MAX)</p>

<p><img src="/images/2016-09-16-Lisbon-summer-camp-mobile-learning-2016/MCS-MAX.jpg" alt="" /></p>

<p>The steps to design the mobile application was really easy. Basically, step by step we created the view dragged and dropped some components like views, lists forms.</p>

<p><img src="/images/2016-09-16-Lisbon-summer-camp-mobile-learning-2016/MCS-MAXCreateViews.jpg" alt="" /></p>

<p>Also we added some charts</p>

<p><img src="/images/2016-09-16-Lisbon-summer-camp-mobile-learning-2016/MCS-MAXCharts.jpg" alt="" /></p>

<p>To include data, first we searched for the API that we published and we selected the version that we wanted to use.</p>

<p><img src="/images/2016-09-16-Lisbon-summer-camp-mobile-learning-2016/MCS-MAXAPI.jpg" alt="" /></p>

<p>Then the fields included in the json schema of the custom API are displayed.</p>

<p><img src="/images/2016-09-16-Lisbon-summer-camp-mobile-learning-2016/MCS-MAXDATA.jpg" alt="" /></p>

<p>Before to deploy in a smartphone, we tested the MAX Application in the MAX simulator. So we clicked on the run icon.</p>

<p><img src="/images/2016-09-16-Lisbon-summer-camp-mobile-learning-2016/MCS-MAXRunSimulator.jpg" alt="" /></p>

<p>We can test the simulator for Android and IOS on different screen sizes.</p>

<p><img src="/images/2016-09-16-Lisbon-summer-camp-mobile-learning-2016/MCS-MAXSimulator.jpg" alt="" /></p>

<p>Then when everything was going fine, we tested on the device, so we clicked on the button “Test on Phone”.</p>

<p><img src="/images/2016-09-16-Lisbon-summer-camp-mobile-learning-2016/MCS-MAXTestPhone.jpg" alt="" /></p>

<p>It gave a QR code generated to use with another application called Oracle Mobile Application Accelerator. We could find in Apple store and Google Play store.</p>

<p><img src="/images/2016-09-16-Lisbon-summer-camp-mobile-learning-2016/MCS-MAXQR.jpg" alt="" /></p>

<p>Once installed and running, we selected the plus icon at the bottom right of the MAX app, this started the QR code scanner. Then we scanned the QR code generated by the app.</p>

<p><img src="/images/2016-09-16-Lisbon-summer-camp-mobile-learning-2016/MCS-MAXQRScanner.jpg" alt="" /></p>

<p>The application was automatically starting after installation. Once the app was closed and we wanted to run it again, we could see that app in the MAX application container.</p>

<p><img src="/images/2016-09-16-Lisbon-summer-camp-mobile-learning-2016/MCS-MAXDeployedApp.jpg" alt="" /></p>
